GIT
1) version control system is a tool that helps to track changes in code.
2) Git is a version control system.

Basically samjhe toh ye ek tarah se history generatre karta hai ki kab koi project add hui kab koi project ka kuch delete hui.

3) it is popular, free and open source, fast and scalable.

Steps or works of Git
1) Track the history.
2) Collaborate.

             GITHUB
Website that allow developer to store and manage their code using git.

https:/github.com

GITHUB Account
1)create a new repository: xyz-demo
2)make our first commit.



+++++++++++++++++Setting up Git++++++++++++++++++
1) Visual Studio Code
2) Windows (Git Bash)
3) Mac (Terminal)

git --version


+++++++++++++++Configuring Git+++++++++++++++++++++++

git configur --global user.name"
git config -- global user.email"Someone@gmail.com"
git config --list

++++++++Clone & Status++++++++++++++++++
Clone = Cloning a repository on our local machine.
        git clone<-some link->

Status = Display the state of the code.
        git status

four types of status

1) untracked
    new files that git doesnot yet track.

2) modified 
    changed

3) staged 
    file. ready to be committed

4) unmodified 
    unchanged

++++++++++++++Add & Commit++++++++++++++++

add = add new or changed file s in your working directory to the git staging area.
    git add<-file name->

commit = it is the record of change 
    git commit-m "some message" 